Average Inhibition at 3.6 uM: Average percent inhibition of the counterscreen at a compound concentration of 3.6 uM.
Standard Deviation: Standard deviation derived from the normalized percent inhibition of the triplicate data for each compound.
Inhibition at 3.6 uM [1]: Percent inhibition of the counterscreen at a compound concentration of 3.6 uM; replicate 1.
Inhibition at 3.6 uM [2]: Percent inhibition of the counterscreen at a compound concentration of 3.6 uM; replicate 2.
Inhibition at 3.6 uM [3]: Percent inhibition of the counterscreen at a compound concentration of 3.6 uM; replicate 3.
